abstract: President Donald Trump railed behind closed doors Thursday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's decision to delay sending articles of impeachment to the Republican Senate, putting an expected trial in limbo.
snippet: President Donald Trump railed behind closed doors Thursday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's decision to delay sending articles of impeachment to the Republican Senate, putting an expected trial in limbo.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump railed behind closed doors Thursday about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's decision to delay sending articles of impeachment to the Republican Senate, putting an expected trial in limbo.
headline_main: Trump Rails Against Delay in Moving Impeachment to Senate
headline_print_headline: Trump Rails Against Delay in Moving Impeachment to Senate

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives passed the second of two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump on Wednesday, voting that Trump obstructed Congress by refusing to cooperate with a Democratic-led impeachment investigation.
snippet: The U.S. House of Representatives passed the second of two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump on Wednesday, voting that Trump obstructed Congress by refusing to cooperate with a Democratic-led impeachment investigation.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. House of Representatives passed the second of two articles of impeachment against President Donald Trump on Wednesday, voting that Trump obstructed Congress by refusing to cooperate with a Democratic-led impeachment investigation.
headline_main: U.S. House Votes to Impeach Trump for Obstruction of Congress
headline_print_headline: U.S. House Votes to Impeach Trump for Obstruction of Congress

abstract: Already comfortable as an outlier in her party, Democratic presidential candidate Tulsi Gabbard did not support the impeachment of President Donald Trump, voting “present” Wednesday on two articles that cleared the House.
snippet: Already comfortable as an outlier in her party, Democratic presidential candidate Tulsi Gabbard did not support the impeachment of President Donald Trump, voting “present” Wednesday on two articles that cleared the House.
lead_paragraph: Already comfortable as an outlier in her party, Democratic presidential candidate Tulsi Gabbard did not support the impeachment of President Donald Trump, voting “present” Wednesday on two articles that cleared the House.
headline_main: Defying Party, Gabbard Votes 'Present' on Trump Impeachment
headline_print_headline: Defying Party, Gabbard Votes 'Present' on Trump Impeachment

abstract: The first line of President Donald Trump’s obituary has been written.

headline_main: Teaching Impeachment: 7 Ideas From Our Readers

abstract: The president traveled to Michigan, a vital electoral state, to deliver his response after he became the third president to be impeached by the House.
snippet: The president traveled to Michigan, a vital electoral state, to deliver his response after he became the third president to be impeached by the House.
lead_paragraph: BATTLE CREEK, Mich. — President Trump angrily responded to the impeachment he had long been dreading on Wednesday, lashing out at his Democratic accusers in a rambling two-hour speech and calling for their defeat in November.
